name: ETHx

name: Morpho USDT (BB)
description: Morpho - "bbUSDT" - USDT lent to a vault which supplies deposited assets to Morpho markets whitelisted by the vault Curator. The Curator can set supply caps of each market. If the supply cap is reached, deposited assets will be supplied to another whitelisted market. This vault is curated by B.Protocol and Block Analitica and is intended to optimize risk-adjusted interest earned from blue-chip collateral markets.

name: Morpho ETH
description: Morpho ETH (Re7) - ETH lent to a vault which supplies deposited assets to Morpho markets whitelisted by the vault Curator. The Curator can set supply caps of each market. If the supply cap is reached, deposited assets will be supplied to another whitelisted market. This vault is curated by Re7 and aims to outperform staked ETH yields by lending WETH against a diverse set of Liquid Staking and Liquid Restaking Token collateral markets.

name: Morpho USDC (Steakhouse)
description: Morpho - "steakUSDC": USDC lent to a vault which supplies deposited assets to Morpho markets whitelisted by the vault Curator. The Curator can set supply caps of each market. If the supply cap is reached, deposited assets will be supplied to another whitelisted market. This vault is curated by Steakhouse Finance and aims to optimize yields by lending USDC against blue chip crypto and real world asset (RWA) collateral markets, depending on market conditions. Steakhouse calls this the “dual engine.”

name: apxETH
description: apxETH is for users focused on maximizing staking yields. After minting pxETH, users can deposit it into Dinero's auto-compounding rewards vault to enjoy boosted staking yields without managing their own validators.

name: Savings DAI
description: Savings DAI (sDAI) - DAI (MakerDAO) deposited on Spark Finance to earn yield via the DAI Savings Rate (DSR). DAI is a decentralized, overcollateralized stablecoin backed by a mix of collateral and reserves. The DSR is a fixed rate of return set by MakerDAO governance which rewards the portion of DAI deposited in a vault. The yield paid out is a share of revenue earned from DAI’s backing assets, either through interest charged on loans, or from deploying reserves.

name: USDM
description:
The USDM token is a rebasing ERC20 token, redeemable at a pegged 1:1 USD value by primary users. USDM is a fully backed stablecoin, backed by "USDM Reserves", which are held under custody with regulated financial institutions in bankruptcy-remote accounts, segregated from the Company's operating accounts, on behalf of, and for the benefit of, Users.

USDM rebases daily, allowing users to receive rewards. These rewards are generated by the interest paid by the US Treasuries held in the USDM Reserves.

name: Staked Frax ETH
description: Staked Frax ETH (sfraxETH) - acts as a stablecoin loosely pegged to ETH, so that 1 frxETH always represents 1 ETH and the amount of frxETH in circulation matches the amount of ETH in the Frax ETH system. sfrxETH is a ERC-4626 vault designed to accrue the staking yield of the Frax ETH validators. At any time, frxETH can be exchanged for sfrxETH by depositing it into the sfrxETH vault, which allows users to earn staking yield on their frxETH. Over time, as validators accrue staking yield, an equivalent amount of frxETH is minted and added to the vault, allowing users to redeem their sfrxETH for a greater amount of frxETH than they deposited
